###
### Phase 3.1 Assisted Search - REST Client Examples
### Compatible with: REST Client (VS Code), Insomnia, PostMan
###
### Usage:
###   1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code
###   2. Set @token = your-jwt-token below
###   3. Right-click on any request and select "Send Request"
###   4. View response in "Response" tab
###

### ============================================================
### CONFIGURATION
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiI0MmNhNzMzMy1iMzdlLTRlMWItYmQ1MC1hYzA0YWJkN2U2ODIiLCJlbWFpbCI6Im1lbm5vLmRyZXNjaGVyQGdtYWlsLmNvbSIsImlhdCI6MTc3MjQ5NTkxOCwiZXhwIjoxNzcyNTgyMzE4fQ.aLmq3cHeYmX-5MSISL2W2eJ5EkH0yc_K8BUUmLgX2q4
@contentType = application/json

### ============================================================
### TEST 1: Context Assembly - Strategic Query
### ============================================================
### Returns enriched context without AI generation
### Good for: Previewing knowledge graph before user submits query

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "What is our AI adoption strategy?",
  "limit": 10,              
  "offset": 0,
  "includeRelationships": true,
  "relationshipDepth": 2
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 2: Context Assembly - Risk Analysis
### ============================================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "Which portfolios have the highest risk?",
  "limit": 10,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeRelationships": true,
  "relationshipDepth": 2
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 3: Assisted Search (JSON) - With AI Answer
### ============================================================
### Returns context + AI-generated answer as JSON
### Good for: Full response at once, simpler parsing

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/assisted-search HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "How should we prioritize our AI transformation roadmap?",
  "limit": 8,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeAnswer": true,
  "stream": false,
  "provider": "google",
  "includeRelationships": true,
  "relationshipDepth": 2
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 4: Assisted Search (JSON) - Dependencies
### ============================================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/assisted-search HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "What are the dependencies between our major programs?",
  "limit": 8,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeAnswer": true,
  "stream": false,
  "includeRelationships": true,
  "relationshipDepth": 2
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 5: Assisted Search (Streaming) - Real-time Tokens
### ============================================================
### Returns context + streams answer tokens via Server-Sent Events
### Good for: Real-time display, long responses, better UX
### Note: REST Client will show streaming chunks as they arrive

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/assisted-search HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "Summarize our key strategic initiatives and their business impact",
  "limit": 8,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeAnswer": true,
  "stream": true,
  "includeRelationships": true,
  "relationshipDepth": 2
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 6: Custom Provider Override - Ollama
### ============================================================
### Force specific AI provider/model for testing fallback behavior

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/assisted-search HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "What is our technology roadmap?",
  "limit": 8,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeAnswer": true,
  "stream": false,
  "provider": "ollama",
  "model": "llama2"
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 7: Limited Results - Quick Response
### ============================================================
### Smaller result set for faster context assembly

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "Digital transformation initiatives",
  "limit": 3,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeRelationships": false
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 8: Pagination - Page 2
### ============================================================
### Skip first 5 results, get next 5

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "transformation initiative",
  "limit": 5,
  "offset": 5,
  "includeRelationships": true
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 9: Deep Relationships - Extended Context
### ============================================================
### relationshipDepth: 3 includes further relationships in enrichment

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "digital transformation",
  "limit": 5,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeRelationships": true,
  "relationshipDepth": 3
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 10: Shallow Relationships - Fast Lightweight Context
### ============================================================
### relationshipDepth: 1 for minimal enrichment

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "digital transformation",
  "limit": 5,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeRelationships": true,
  "relationshipDepth": 1
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 11: Entity Type Filtering - Only Projects
### ============================================================
### Focus search on specific entity types

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "cloud migration",
  "limit": 10,
  "offset": 0,
  "types": ["project"],
  "includeRelationships": true
}


### ============================================================
### TEST 12: Custom System Prompt - Override Instructions
### ============================================================
### Inject custom instructions for AI response generation

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/assisted-search HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "What is our top AI risk?",
  "limit": 8,
  "offset": 0,
  "includeAnswer": true,
  "stream": false,
  "systemPrompt": "You are a risk management expert. Focus on identifying mitigation strategies."
}


### ============================================================
### NEGATIVE TEST 1: Missing Authentication
### ============================================================
### Should return 401 Unauthorized

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "test"
}


### ============================================================
### NEGATIVE TEST 2: Empty Query
### ============================================================
### Should return 400 Bad Request - query is required

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "",
  "limit": 10
}


### ============================================================
### NEGATIVE TEST 3: Invalid Token
### ============================================================
### Should return 401 Unauthorized

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/context-assembly HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token-xyz
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "test query",
  "limit": 10
}


### ============================================================
### HEALTH CHECK
### ============================================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/health HTTP/1.1


### ============================================================
### TIPS FOR USING REST CLIENT
### ============================================================
###
### 1. Update @token variable:
###    Click the REST Client settings and add:
###    "rest-client.environmentVariables": {
###      "$shared": {
###        "token": "your-actual-jwt-token"
###      }
###    }
###
### 2. View response timeline:
###    Right-click response → Copy
###    Look at response time metrics
###
### 3. Test different response modes:
###    • Set stream: false for full JSON
###    • Set stream: true to see SSE chunks
###
### 4. Check response headers:
###    Click "Headers" tab in response panel
###    For streaming: Content-Type: text/event-stream
###
### 5. Measure latency:
###    Watch "Response Time" in bottom status bar
###    Expected: 300-500ms for context, 1-3s with AI
###
### 6. Debug with custom headers:
###    Add: X-Debug-Mode: true
###    Check server logs for [RAG] debug output
###
### 7. Batch test multiple queries:
###    Select multiple requests and run with Ctrl+Alt+L
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/assisted-search
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "How should we prioritize our AI transformation roadmap?",
  "includeAnswer": true,
  "stream": false
}
